node.text:
We're kicking off our first est film production with a momentous Malvern Home renovation by @dohertydesignstudio from est magazine issue #35.
.
Tapping into its rich architectural past and 1980s new wave bones, @dohertydesignstudio have skilfully commandeered an epic journey to reinvent this Melbourne family home. An original 1980's design by architect Peter McIntyre. .
.
Experience the entire home via the link in profile or read the full feature in est magazine issue #35. .
.
Design @dohertydesignstudio
Building design @arialexander
Builder @north_building_group 
Styling @heathernetteking 
Florals and assitant styling @rachelpolivkastylist 
Art consultant @gb.art.consulting 
Landscape design @benscott_design 
Videography @richardlipp.studio
Words @meganmayrawson
Art @tompolo @liamsnootle @anyapesce @oocaleb @davidjamesgriggs @christianthompsonartist #leekyoung-hwa 
Furniture & Objects @domoaustralia @lightlydesign @loomtowels @fenton_and_fenton @abode_living @moderntimesau @ajarfurniture @lamarzoccohomeau

node.text:
Great land. Great architecture. Great living. In an est exclusive, we feature three unique films by Rob Mills Architecture & Interiors (RMA). Australian-based RMA’s latest project, a ground-breaking residence in Byron Bay incorporates Mill’s signature use of drama, curves, lines, light and a reflection of the qualities of the land.
.
View all three films via link in profile.
.
Videography @collider__
Creative Direction | Design @robmillsarchitects

node.title: Exclusive | The latest architectural project by Rob Mills

node.text:
HOME TOUR | Alma House
​.
​As a complete reimagining, Alma House sees the remodelling of an existing building from the inside out. 
​.
​Taking cues from the site’s storied past and creating new connections internally, @atelierbarda carve out a subdued home that feels far removed – and readily connected – at once to its Montreal setting.
​.
​Read more about the Alma House on estliving.com – link in profile. 
​.
​Design @atelierbarda 
​Photography @alexlesage__
​Words @bronwynmarshall 
​.
​https://www.estliving.com/alma-house-atelier-barda/

node.text:
MONDAY MUSE | Yvonne Kone
​.
Danish accessories designer Yvonne Kone opens the doors to her Copenhagen apartment, mirroring the same effortless style as her namesake label.
​.
As this week's Monday Muse, we explore Yvonne’s personal interior style, where she spends most of her time, her favourite materials and design objects and how her home has become a source of inspiration. 
​.
​See more of Yvonne's home on estliving.com via the link in profile.
​.
​Design @yvonnekone 
​Photography @linethitklein 
​.
https://www.estliving.com/my-space-yvonne-kone/

node.text:
AT HOME WITH | Chan & Eayrs
​.
@chanandeayrs converted this loft space in London's Shoreditch by favouring tactility and custom details – from the natural oak kitchen joinery to the linen shutters above the bath. 
​.
Standout pieces in their home include the iconic Camaleonda sofa, designed in 1970 by Mario Bellini and The Water Monopoly Rockwell bath that reflects the serene mint green thread throughout. 
​.
​Design @chanandeayrs
​Photography @_martin_morrell
​.
​https://www.estliving.com/

​.

node.text:
FEATURED HOME | Force of Nature 
​.
​S​itting sculpturally in its arid and unaltered surrounding landscape, Casa M – @vincentvanduysen's Portuguese holiday home – is subtly disguised among its terrain. 
​.
​Emerging from the ground some three years after the initial sketch, the resulting structure draws on the key essentialist principles that underpin @vincentvanduysen's work, while fusing an appropriate vein of Brutalism as a welcomed response to context.
​.
See more of @vincentvanduysen's holiday home in the latest issue of est Magazine – link in profile.
​.
​Design @vincentvanduysen
​Photography @ricardolabougle
​Words @bronwynmarshall
​.
​https://www.estliving.com/magazine/est-magazine-issue-41/

node.text:
FRIDAY FACADES | Three Idyllic Residences in Spain
​.
 Among the four Balearic Islands (and the smallest of the lot) sits Formentera. This exclusive island, its pristine coastlines and petite villages are where you go to escape the crowds and revel in some peace and quiet.
​.
So what better place to design three family homes, in an olive grove overlooking the ocean, connected by dirt roads? That’s what Barcelona-based firm GCA Architects were called to do, combining linear Mediterranean architecture, minimalist principles and the island’s natural materials.
​.
See behind the facade on estliving.com via the link in profile.
​.
​Design @gcaarchitects
​Photography @salvalopez
​.
https://www.estliving.com/gca-spanish-residences/

THE EDIT | Coloured Bedroom Carpet
​.
​Colourful carpet can dramatically enhance the warmth, mood and elegance of a space. 
​.
​Whether it’s subtly pulling together interior elements, or creating visual impact, we explore why coloured carpets are experiencing a resurgence, through seven striking bedroom spaces.
